# Regression: fuzz seed 306. Push-loop fusion caches an array's data/len/cap in
# C locals across the loop and writes the descriptor back only at loop exit. A
# closure created INSIDE the loop captures the array by value at creation time;
# the env build must not read the stale (pre-loop) descriptor. tychoc fused the
# loop because count_reads didn't see lambda captures as reads -> cl() returned
# the pre-loop len (3) every iteration instead of the value at creation.
# Correct: iterations capture len 3, 4, 5 -> acc 12; final len 6.
fn main():
    acc := 0
    v := [1, 2, 3]
    for i in range(3):
        cl := fn() -> int: len(v)
        push(v, 1)
        acc = acc + cl()
    print(str(acc) + "\n")
    print(str(len(v)) + "\n")
